  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Children in Charge of Change (India)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In some slum areas of Bhavnagar, India, over two-thirds of school age children miss out on an education which could lift them out of poverty and protect them from child labour. Of those who are in school, the majority never finish their education and are vulnerable to hazardous jobs such as working as gem polishers. The project aims to build on a successful local model of child and youth collectives comprising those who are in school, non-school going and working. These collectives help them to build their self-esteem and provide peer support that retains them in school and away from child labour. Weekly visits to their homes ensure a dialogue with families to deal with obstacles to children&apos;s progress. As a result more children will work for fewer hours, and receive a good quality education and the model may prove replicable across the state of Gujarat and beyond.</narrative>
  </description>
